The number of individuals receiving
help for over-indebtedness from the Portuguese Association for
Consumer Protection rose 24 percent in the nine months through
September from the same period a year earlier, DECO said today.  A total of 4,010 people are being assisted by the consumer
protection group, up from 3,238 in the previous month, it said
in an e-mailed report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
